The paper deals with natural language processing and database querying, which are both topics that fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the accuracy of SQL generation, which is a task related to databases (cs.DB). The use of neural networks and machine learning also suggests that the paper could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, as it aims to map natural language questions to SQL queries, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
